With almost six months to go until the opening ceremony of the 2022 Hangzhou Asian Games, the organizers have announced that construction of all the 56 venues for the games is now complete.A total of 56 competition facilities will be used during Hangzhou 2022, including 12 newly-built venues, and 44 renovated and temporary facilities. In addition, 31 training venues and five Asian Games Villages are also ready for service. All the venues are ready for a green and smart Asian Games. The Asian Games' 19th edition will be held in Hangzhou, capital of east China's Zhejiang Province, from September 10 to 25, followed by the fourth Asian Para Games from October 9 to 15. This will be the third Asian Games to be hosted in China, after Beijing 1990 and Guangzhou 2010.